    A abstract general purpose writable where the actual class represented is composed of a number of Node instances

    The binary encoding of this base implementation is just a variable integer indicating the number of nodes present followed by the binary encodings of the NodeWritable instances. Derived implementations may wish to override the readFields(DataInput) and write(DataOutput) methods in order to use more specialised encodings.
